Janet A. Craig is Vice President, Investor Relations.

Ms. Craig joined the Fortis Group in 2015 with more than 20 years in the investor relations field. She was Senior Vice President of Investor Relations for Loblaw Companies Limited and Vice President of Investor Relations for Nexen Inc., a global energy company based in Calgary. She also managed investor relations for Nortel Networks.

She earned a Bachelor of Arts (Anthropology and English) from the University of Toronto. 

Ms. Craig serves on the Editorial Advisory Board of IR Magazine and is a frequent speaker on investor relations and shareholder engagement, including IR Think Tanks and Executive Management Programs. She holds numerous awards and recognition for investor relations, including over 20 #1 awards in Canada. In 2012 Janet was named one of the “Top 25 Investor Relations Officers of All Time” in a global ranking of investor relations officers by Investor Relations magazine.  


 

Karen J. Gosse is Vice President of Planning and Forecasting of Fortis.

Ms. Gosse’s career with the Fortis Group spans more than a decade. She was Vice
President and Chief Financial Officer of Fortis Properties from 2013-2015. She joined
the Fortis organization in 2004 as an Internal Auditor at Fortis Properties, and in 2005
was appointed Manager, Financial Reporting with Fortis, a position she held for eight
years.

Ms. Gosse earned a Bachelor of Commerce (Honours) from Memorial University
of Newfoundland and is a member of the Association of Chartered Professional
Accountants of Newfoundland and Labrador.


Ms. Gosse serves on the Board of Directors of Gymnastics Newfoundland and Labrador.  


 

Regan O’Dea is Vice President, General Counsel.

Mr. O’Dea joined Fortis Inc. in 2014. Previously, he worked in private practice in Newfoundland and Labrador where he represented the interests of Fortis Inc., and in-house with a national insurance company where he served as Director, Legal and Corporate Services.
Mr. O’Dea graduated from Mount Allison University with a Bachelor of Science in Biology and Physics in 1997 and from the University of New Brunswick with a Bachelor of Laws in 2000. He was admitted to the Law Society of Newfoundland and Labrador in 2001. Mr. O’Dea has his CIC.C designation (Certified In-House Counsel-Canada) having contributed to the program's early development and has worked as part-time faculty at Memorial University business school.  
Mr. O’Dea is active in the community coaching youth soccer, and previously served as President of the Newfoundland Chapter of the Canadian Corporate Counsel Association (CCCA) and member of certain national committees.  


 

James D. Spinney is Vice President and Treasurer of Fortis.

Mr. Spinney’s career with the Fortis Group spans more than two-and-a-half decades.
From 1990 to 2002 he held the positions of Auditor, Treasurer and Manager of
Regulatory Affairs at Newfoundland Power. In 2002, he was appointed Manager
of Treasury of Fortis and in 2013, Mr. Spinney was appointed Vice President and
Treasurer of Fortis.

He earned a Bachelor of Science from Memorial University of Newfoundland and
is a member of the Association of Professional Accountants of Newfoundland and
Labrador.  


 

James D. Roberts is Vice President and Controller of Fortis.

Mr. Roberts’ career with the Fortis Group spans more than a decade. In 2004, he
was appointed Manager of Corporate Planning at Newfoundland Power, where he
successively held the position of Treasurer. In 2008, he was appointed Vice President
and Chief Financial Officer, Fortis Properties. In 2013, Mr. Roberts was appointed
Vice President, Controller of Fortis.

He earned a Bachelor of Commerce (Honours) from Memorial University of
Newfoundland and is a member of the Association of Chartered Professional
Accountants of Newfoundland and Labrador.  












