He earned a Bachelor of Engineering (Electrical) degree from Memorial University of Newfoundland.


Mr. Delaney currently serves on the Board of Directors of FortisBC. He previously served on the Board of Directors of Newfoundland Power, the Canadian Electricity Association, the Western Energy Institute, and Honens, a Calgary-based arts organization. He has also served as a member of the Dean’s Advisory Council to the Faculty of Engineering and Applied Science at Memorial University of Newfoundland. 
